@WaffleLapkin, I add `raw` mod as in your [minimal solution](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=c241ac12727c0300376e91ddbcd63bc8), but have changed copy-pasting of types' fields in enums to using concrete types in variants:

```rust
struct Voice {
  pub id: String,

  #[serde(flatten)]
  pub kind: VoiceKind,

  pub title: String,
   pub caption: Option<String>,
}

enum VoiceKind {
  Cached {
    voice_file_id: String,
  },
  Remote {
    voice_url: Url,
     voice_duration: Option<Seconds>,
  },
}
```
=>
```rust
enum VoiceKind {
  Cached(CahedVoice),
  NonCached(Voice),
}
```

This shorter and simplify using in `From`. I'm not sure if it has any sense, which I didn't understand.

